      <div id="content">
        
  <div class="column_holder">
    <h1>
      <img alt="JOBS" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=JOBS" />
    </h1>
    <div class="column_heading">
      <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblTop"><p>GRIN is constantly looking for talented people. All available positions are listed below. Apply via the form or by e-mail.  If you are interested in a position that isn&rsquo;t listed, please send your CV via e-mail to jobs@grin.se.</p></span></div>
    <div class="column_sep">
      <img src="img/jobs/jobs_open_sep.png" alt="Open positions" /></div>
    
    
      <div class="column_content">
        <h1>
          <img alt="Friday 26 October 2007" src="/images/headers/pf_small/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Friday 26 October 2007" />
        </h1>
        <h2>
          <img alt="Special Effects Artist" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Special Effects Artist" />
        </h2>
        <p>
          <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText"><p>A successful performer in this role, ideally, this will be combined with an in-depth knowledge of the gaming community and an intuitive understanding of the artistic concepts and images that will appeal to existing customers.<br />
<br />
<strong>RESPONSIBILITIES<br />
</strong></p>
<ul type="square">
    <li>Work closely with effects programmers.</li>
    <li>Create all aspects of 2D and 3D game effects. This includes particlesystems, animating textures, polygonal effects meshes, and assets that may be used procedurally by programmers.</li>
    <li>May contribute to design and/or conceptualization efforts as needed.</li>
    <li>Help create foundational particle systems for game engine using proprietary tools.</li>
    <li>Create polygonal and texture effects assets to be used by programmers.</li>
    <li>Work closely with programmers to ensure visual quality of procedural effects.</li>
    <li>Using 3D software, simulate and render animations of in-game effects as proof-of-concept for current and future hardware.</li>
    <li>Create realistic effects such as fire, smoke, and explosions using limited game resources.</li>
    <li>Meet project deadlines/milestones as set by project leads.</li>
    <li>Actively participate in team/department meetings.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>EXPECTATIONS<br />
</strong></p>
<ul type="square">
    <li>Ability to model and texture in 3D.</li>
    <li>Experience with particle effects.</li>
    <li>Minimum of two years of applicable industry experience.</li>
    <li>Strong technical aptitude related to 3D modeling tools and game engine technologies.</li>
    <li>Fluent knowledge of Maya, Max and Photoshop.</li>
    <li>Graphic design or fine art skills a plus.</li>
    <li>Experience with programming or scripting languages a plus.</li>
    <li>Experience with motion picture quality rendered effects a plus.</li>
    <li>Ability to be receptive to art direction and to perform well within a collaborative team environment.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>DEMO REEL REQUIREMENTS</strong><br />
Samples that demonstrate 3D effects work (online, CD or DVD format) - muzzle flashes, explosions, smoke, fire etc. Applicants must provide demo reel/CD/DVD or website address to be considered for any artist position <br />
<br />
<strong>Positions in Stockholm and Gothenburg.</strong></p></span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="column_nav">
        <span class="column_nav_cat">Contact</span>
        <p>
          Please send your application through the online form below, or by regular mail to
          our physical adress. If you prefer to send your application by email click
          <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#106;&#111;&#98;&#64;&#103;&#114;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#115;&#101;">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
